title: List of prime ministers of Canada - Wikipedia
snippet: Two prime ministers have died in office: John A. Macdonald (1867–1873, 1878–1891) and John Thompson (1892–1894), both of natural causes. All others have resigned, either after losing an election or upon retirement. Canadian custom is to count by the individuals who were prime minister, not by terms.

title: Prime Ministers of Canada
snippet: This page provides general details on Canada's prime ministers since 1867.

title: List of prime ministers of Canada | Britannica
snippet: After a general election, the governor-general calls on the leader of the political party winning the most seats in the House of Commons to become prime minister and to form a government. This is a chronologically ordered list of the prime ministers, from the earliest to the most recent.
